I was really excited about this app, I took the time to watch the meetings on YouTube to get ideas on how to better my experience. Some of the info was very helpful and I felt like I had a community. When it comes down to the actual process, I felt that it didn't live up to expectations. I ordered my first test product 4 days ago and I still cannot track the order. They give me a tracking number and it keeps saying unable to track. I am really glad I did this before anyone ordered from me because I would hate to come off looking like a fraud. I am a bit pissed because I spent all this time marketing the items and listing them in different places now I have to go back and remove them. Time wasted, but that's my fault because I should have ordered the test first. Also for the 1st tier-paid subscription, you really don't get a lot of benefits. I would think that they would offer really good benefits which would make people organically want to move to the next tier.

The Zendrop App itself is very well made and user-friendly. But other than that delivery times have been pretty ok so far (mostly 15-16 days) with some delays here and there. Also Thank You cards haven't been working so far and order credits don't show up (maybe because I'm on the trial of the Plus Plan). Anyways supportwise though, it's perfect. Theresa, Molly and ESPECIALLY Michael have been a really big help overcoming those issues and are always here for me if there are any more. They really seem to care about my business and are understanding and (I think is also a really big point) fluent in English! Overall okay Dropshipping service with perfect support. Again, thank you Michael for everything!
